<p>
<seg id=1> Nicaraguan Ambassador to USA Sakasa appealed to the creditor nations to reduce or remit the debts of Central American countries and to provide great assistance for the reconstruction of these countries in order to pull them through the damage from the hurricane Micky. </seg>
<seg id=2> Sakasa indicated to the US television station that the reconstruction of Nicaragua needs about 1 billion US dollars, and he urged the US and other creditor nations to make an overall plan of economic assistance similar to the Michel plan of reconstructing West Europe after the War. </seg>
</p>
